{"id":"257003646_A_note_on_the_average_shadowing_property_for_expansive_maps","abstract":"Let f be a continuous map of a compact metric space. Assuming shadowing for f we relate the average shadowing property of f to transitivity and its variants. Our results extend and complete the work of Sakai [K. Sakai, Various shadowing properties for positively expansive maps, Topology Appl. 131 (2003) 15–31].","authors":["Dominik Kwietniak","Piotr Oprocha"],"meta":["January 2012Topology and its Applications 159(1):19–27","DOI:10.1016/j.topol.2011.04.016"],"references":["233043773_Spectral_Decomposition_Theorem_for_non-hyperbolic_maps","268551518_Weak_mixing_and_product_recurrence","267144134_On_the_average-shadowing_property","265958716_Discreteness_and_continuity_in_problems_of_chaotic_dynamics_Transl_from_the_author_from_an_original_Russian_manuscript","265462357_Topological_theory_of_dynamical_sytems_Recent_advances","265367914_Topological_entropy_and_axiom_A","261826579_Dynamical_Systems_Disjoint_from_Any_Minimal_System","251474104_The_average-shadowing_property_and_strong_ergodicity","248117602_Topological_theory_of_dynamical_systems","243719441_Ergodic_Theory_on_Compact_Spaces","243100885_Deterministic_Properties_of_Stochastically_Perturbed_Dynamic_Systems","238296490_Periodic_Points_and_Measures_for_Axiom_a_Diffeomorphisms","231873998_Metric_properties_of_e-trajectories_of_dynamical_systems_with_stochastic_behaviour","223139367_Various_shadowing_properties_for_positively_expansive_maps","1734907_Chain_recurrence_rates_and_topological_entropy"]}